From 3e15138bf0a58206f2f38f6e211f4da8d7cdb7f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 18:35:30 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 163/174] sh: update_mmu_cache_range() must seed every sub-PTE
 under PGCL

sh's update_mmu_cache_range() ignored its @nr argument and only ran
__update_cache()/__update_tlb() for the first PTE (@address/*ptep). It never
got the page-clustering conversion that mips and the other software-TLB / VIPT
arches have: PGCL's do_anonymous_page()/wp_page_copy() install PAGE_MMUCOUNT
sub-PTEs per kernel page and call update_mmu_cache_range(.., nr) to seed the
arch MMU cache for each (the contract from "mm: insert arch MMU cache for every
sub-PTE installed by anon/COW clustering"). On sh4 only the faulting sub-PTE got
its dcache purge + TLB entry seeded; the other PAGE_MMUCOUNT-1 sub-PTEs of the
cluster were valid in the page tables but left unseeded -- a latent VIPT
dcache-coherency / TLB-refill gap.

Loop over @nr exactly like mips's update_mmu_cache_range(), advancing ptep and
address by MMUPAGE_SIZE per sub-PTE. MMUPAGE_SIZE == PAGE_SIZE at
PAGE_MMUSHIFT == 0, so this is identical to the previous single-PTE behaviour on
a non-PGCL build (Newton limit). Build-verified ARCH=sh PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4.

(Note: a separate sh4 PGCL anon COW-write fault -- the COW of a non-zero
sub-offset sub-PTE within a cluster -- is still under investigation and is not
addressed here.)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01UkhHXA2PvPb3uwymHGbYh8
---
 arch/sh/include/asm/pgtable.h | 12 +++++++++---
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/sh/include/asm/pgtable.h b/arch/sh/include/asm/pgtable.h
index d5ce0950a323..a2ab5f26fbc8 100644
--- a/arch/sh/include/asm/pgtable.h
+++ b/arch/sh/include/asm/pgtable.h
@@ -98,9 +98,15 @@ static inline void update_mmu_cache_range(struct vm_fault *vmf,
 		struct vm_area_struct *vma, unsigned long address,
 		pte_t *ptep, unsigned int nr)
 {
-	pte_t pte = *ptep;
-	__update_cache(vma, address, pte);
-	__update_tlb(vma, address, pte);
+	for (;;) {
+		pte_t pte = *ptep;
+		__update_cache(vma, address, pte);
+		__update_tlb(vma, address, pte);
+		if (--nr == 0)
+			break;
+		ptep++;
+		address += MMUPAGE_SIZE;
+	}
 }
 #define update_mmu_cache(vma, addr, ptep) \
 	update_mmu_cache_range(NULL, vma, addr, ptep, 1)
